data.description: Well built brick home located on 1 and a half acres of land with mature trees near Surf City beaches.  The front of the home has a large patio surrounded by a low brick wall, and leads to a rocking chair front porch.  Inside, the foyer separates the living room and the formal dining room.  The kitchen is located off the dining room.  It features tons of cabinet space, bar seating and a breakfast nook. The large family room has a gas fireplace with a brick hearth and built in shelves on either side.  It also has a built in desk with shelving that is partially closed off from the rest of the room by a 1/2 wall. There are 3 bedrooms and an additional room that can be used as a study or office. The back patio has an outdoor brick fireplace. The back yard is fenced and has a very nice storage shed and a separate workshop with electric. The home has a paved parking pad, a carport, and garage. No shortage of storage space here. Additional features include cedar lined closets, vapor barrier and dehumidifier in the crawl space, electrical outlet for plug in generator, all but 2 windows have been replaced and come with a lifetime warranty, 2 year old water softener, filtration system, and 3 and 1/2 year old HVAC with a 10 year warranty. This home is very well maintained with loads of space and potential!
